help_define('_HELP_IEDITATTRSELECTION',     "=Select attribute=\n\nAttributes are pre-defined characteristics to which records may be allocated e.g. a language or a country.\n\nClick on the symbol \"Select\" of the list of attributes you want to modify in mask [[ieditrecords|Edit records]].\n\nA list of all available attributes will appear. Select the appropriate attribute by clicking on the name of the attribute (or you can apply any search options which also appear in mask [[ioverviewrecords|Records overview]]).\n\nTo delete an attribute, click on the checkbox to the left of the attribute you want to remove.\n\nTo speed up the process of entering attributes, you can also enter attributes as text.  You can pre-set the method of entry and the applicable [[iseperators|Seperator]] form of any attribute type you want to record under [[isettings|Settings / Direct input]].\n\nFinally, you can also define [[inewrecord|new records]] in the attributes table by clicking on the \"New\" symbol  - provided you have been authorised to do so.  NB: A new attribute that has been set must be added to the record via \"Select\".");
help_define('_HELP_IEDITRECORDS',           "=Edit records=\n\nTo edit a record, you must first select the table where the record is located from the [[imainmenu|main menu]] or from [[ioverviewtables|Overview of tables]]. \n\nThis will take you to [[ioverviewrecords|overview of tables]].\n\nThen select the record to be edited by setting the pop-up menu at the top left-hand side at, for example \"ID\". Then enter your ID in the adjacent field and, finally, confirm your selection with  \"OK\". Then click on the relevant record.\n\nProvided you have authorisation, you can now edit the record:\n\n- You can modddify text fields either directly in the mask or using [[ieditor|Editor]].\n- You can [[iactivaterecords|activate records]] or cancel the activation.\n- You can allocate or remove attributes, see [[ieditattrselection|select attributes]].\n- You can modify the structure of the record, see [[irecordstructure|Record structure]].\n- You can modify the rights of the record, see  [[irightsofrecords|rights]].\n\nWhen you are satisfied with your modifications, click on \"OK\" or \"Apply\" at the foot of the page (the first option will bring you back to [[ioverviewrecords|overview of records]], if you select the second option you will remain in the Editor mask). \n\nIf you want to reject the modifications, simply click on \"Cancel\" (this will also take you back to [[ioverviewrecords|Apply]]).\n\nFinally, in the [[imainmenu|main menu]], in addition to the option to skip directly to the previous/next record, also provides you with the following options, (providing you  have the right form for the relevant action): \n\n- [[inewrecord|New]]\n- [[iempty|Empty]]\n- [[icopyrecords|Copy]]\n- [[ideleterecords|Delete]]\n- [[ireferencesofrecords|References]]\n- [[iview|View]]\n- [[isettings|Settings]]");
