help_define('_HELP_IIDS0',                  "=IDs=\n\nThe programme interprets an ID as a unique number identifying a record contained in a table, and no two records from one table can have the same ID, although two records from different tables can still share the same ID.\n\nA record can therefore be identified through its table and its ID.  The ID is valid until the record is [[ideleterecords|deleted]].\n\nThe system allocates the IDs itself and ensures that they are unique.  The user is not involved in this process.  The IDs may, however, be appled from another web-page, e.g. from a Portal.\n\nThe IDs of a record are shown in masks [[ioverviewrecords|overview of records]]\nand [[ieditrecords|Edit records]].");
help_define('_HELP_IIMPORT8',               "=Import=\n\nYou can import records in SQL Format into the system. To do this, an SQL Dump must be transferred in a file, so that the individual SQL commands have to  be separated by a semi-colon (You can obtain an SQL Dump from the system itself under \"Export\").\n\n\nThe file with the SQL Dump can be either up-loaded or specified through a path. If specified through a path it will already be located on the server in any case and, for example, transferred by FTP.\n\n\nWarning: If the wrong SQL Dump is imported this can destroy your entire database!\n\nBoth import and export processes can take some time.");
