help_define('_HELP_IOVERVIEWRECORDS',       "=Overview of records=\n\nTo obtain an overview of the records contained in a table, you must first select the relevant table from [[imainmenu|main menu]] or [[ioverviewtables|overview of tables]].\n\nThis takes you to a mask displaying all or part of the records contained in the table you have selected. \n\nAt the top of this mask, you can vary the choice of records to be displayed. Select the field in which you want to search from the pop-up menu (eg. \"ID\" or \"Name\") and then enter the value you are searching (eg. \"12\" oder \"Miller\"). The fields available from the pop-up menu depend on the table in which you are searching.\n\nWhen you click on \"OK\" the programme will search for all records with the relevant criteria and provide them in a list with several columns (you can set the columns you want displayed using [[isettings|Settings]] and you can also insert or remove the [[ireferencesofrecords|References]] column).\n\nIf the search results in more records than can be displayed on the screen, you can use the buttons in the menu at the top to turn the pages forwards and backwards. Alternatively, you can vary the number of records to be displayed simultaneously through the field \"Lines\". \n\nBy clicking on the title of a column, the selection - where possible -is ordered according to the criterion in the title and another click on the same heading reverses the order. The arrows indicate the order in use (if no arrows are visible, the records are arranged according to a field which has not yet been inserted. If need be, switch over to it using [[isettings|Settings]]).\n\nFinally, the following additional options are available using the [[imainmenu|main menu]]\n(assuming you have been authorised to carry out the relevant activity): \n\n-[[inewrecord|New]]\n-[[iempty|Empty]]\n-[[iallrecords|All]] (displays all records and orders them according to the date they were modified)  \n-[[iexport|Import/Export]]\n-[[isettings|Settings]]\n\nA few more comments on the options available through the pop-up menu and the adjacent text field:\n\n-You can also use wildcard \"*\" in the text field, eg.  \"Mil*\" for \"Miller\" or \"Million\"\n-For records fields (eg. \"Creted\" or \"Modified\") you can type in the record using normal dates. You can also give an area.\n- You can also combine search criterias using the button \"Expand search\".");
help_define('_HELP_IOVERVIEWTABLES',        "=Overview of tables=\n\nYou will find an overview of all tables and the access rights available to you in relation to each table under \"Etc.\" in the [[imainmenu|main menu]]. Click on the name of a table to reach [[ioverviewrecords|\noverview of records]] for that table.\n\nThe individual overview columns are:\n\n- Name - name of the table\n- Rights - your access rights in relation to the table\n- Type - table type:\n-- Primary data - the records contained in the table are used primarily as basic data. Primary data are in the main accessible through the [[imainmenu|main menu]].\n-- Secondary data - the records in the table are (also) used as secondary data for primary tables, see [[irecordstructure|record structure]]\n-- Attribute - the records in the table are (also) used as attributes of primary or secondary tables, eg. for links \n- Modified - when was the last time a record in this table was modified?\n- Entries - The number of entries ie. records in this table \n- Ref. - Total [[ireferencesofrecords|References]] (or inverted links) of all records in this table, ie. how many records in this or other tables refer to the records in this table?\n\nFinally, you will also find data at the foot of the page as to the last modification made in any of the tables, ie. this is the last date in the column \"Modified\".");
