help_define('_HELP_ISETTINGS',              "=Settings=\n\nTo create or modify your personal settings, click on \"Your settings\" in the\n[[imainmenu|main menu]].\n\nThe options that appear will depend on the mask you were in: \n\n- Mask [[ieditrecords|edit records]] - this is where you can set the size of the text fields, the [[ieditattrselection|attribute selection]] and whether you want to use the  [[ieditor|editor]].\n- Mask [[ioverviewrecords|overview of records]] - This is where you can set the columns you want and the size of the field for entering search criteria.\n\nMoreover, you'll find some common settings eg. for the filter, the view or for your password here.\n\nTo save the settings click on \n\"OK\" or \"Apply\" at the bottom of the page. If you click on \"OK\"\nyou will return to the page you were on previously and if you click on \"Apply\" you will stay in the settings mask.  The settings will be stored permanently on the server and will still be available next time you log on, irrespective of which computer or [[ibrowser|Browser]] you are using. \n\nIf you click on \"Cancel\" you will return to the page you were on before, without saving the settings.\n\nImportant note: These settings only apply to the user who is logged on at the time, so that the programme is adapted to that user´s individual preferences. Other users can have other settings.");
help_define('_HELP_ISETTINGS0',             "");
help_define('_HELP_ISETTINGSCOLUMNS',       "=Edit Columns=\n\nYou can define the columns you want to see in the mask [[ioverviewrecords | \"overview records\"]].");
help_define('_HELP_ISETTINGSFIELDS',        "=Edit Search Fields=\n\nYou can define the filds you want to use for search in the mask [[ioverviewrecords | \"overview records\"]].");
help_define('_HELP_ISETTINGSFILTER',        "=Filter=\n\nYou can filter some groups of records that should not be displayed in the mask [[ioverviewrecords | \"overview records\"]].\n\nUse [[isettings | \"Your settings]] - Filter\" for this purpose.");
help_define('_HELP_ISETTINGSINPUT',         "=Input Fields=\n\nYou can define the size of the input fields in the mask [[ieditrecords | \"edit records\"]]. The size can be defined separatly for each table and each field.\n\nUse [[isettings | \"Your setting]] - Input fields\" for this purpose.");
help_define('_HELP_ISETTINGSJOBS',          "=Jobs=\n\nJob lists can be used to organize records in seperate lists.\n\nTo edit job lists, use [[isettings | \"Your Settings]] - Jobs\".");
help_define('_HELP_ISETTINGSPASSWORD',      "=Password=\n\nYou can choose your own password and change it at any time. To do this, click on \"Settings / Passwort\" in [[imainmenu|main menu]].\n\nA mask will appear in which you will be asked to enter your existing password and then the new password underneath, which you will enter twice. The password will not be displayed on the screen.\n\nThe reason you have to enter your existing password is to prevent an unauthorised person from altering your password if you have logged on and left your desk for a moment. \n\nThe new password has to be entered twice to ensure there are no typing errors. Use of upper and lower case is relevant to this. \n\nThe modification will be complete when you click on \"OK\" or \"Apply\". If you click on \"Cancel\" the action is ended without any change to your password.\n\nA few comments on security:\n\nAvoid use of passwords that can be guessed by someone who knows you even slightly - name of spouse, children, even pets should be prohibited, as should birthdays, marriage dates, \netc.\n\nA variation of known information such as \"login name\", \n\"name\", or \"name backwards\", can easily be guessed by an intruder and they can all be  tried out quickly.\n\nWords found in various dictionaries used by professional hackers are also a security risk. They can be used to try out thousands of words systematically.\n\nPasswords such as \"123456\", \"qwert\" or \"asdfg\"\netc. are automatically disqualified.\n\nThe safest passwords are those which do not make up a real word, using upper and lower case, together with a few numbers. Of course, you also have to be able to remember it. If you write the password down - or use a browser to remember it -  all your efforts in selecting a password will virtually be negated.  \n\nDo not give your password to anyone, absolutely NO-ONE, including the supervisor.  The supervisor does not know your password, but if there are problems (eg. if you forget your password), the supervisor can allocate a new password without knowing the old one. \n\nThese rules do not apply only to this programme, PC/CMS, \nbut are relevant to all other passwords.");
help_define('_HELP_ISETTINGSSEARCH',        "=Search Settings=\n\nYou can define settings for the search in the mask [[ieditrecords | \"edit records\"]].\n\nUse [[isettings | \"Your setting]] - Search settings\" for this purpose.");
help_define('_HELP_ISETTINGSVIEW',          "=View Settings=\n\nYou can define several settings for the view, the look of the program.\n\nUse [[isettings | \"Your setting]] - View\" for this purpose.");
