help_define('_HELP_ISYSLOC8',               "=System localisation=\n\n'''System localisation''' enables you to modify all strings applied by the programme, to add new languages and to administer existing ones. \n\nIf you have been given authorisation, you can access system localisation under \"Etc. / System localisation\".\n\nThe strings used by the programme are divided into various '''Module''', and you can select the module you want to modify at the top left-hand side. The module for system localisation itself, for example, is called \"admin/lang/sysloc\". A module can contain as many entries as you like in as many languages as you like and, by using the  '''languages =''' option, you can display up to three languages at once. \n\nThe various modules are broadly divided into the areas '''config''' (table-specific strings) and '''admin''' (system-specific strings). In that context, the module \"admin/lang/basic\" is especially important, in that it is the languages that are used in this module that determine the languages available in  [[iloginlogout|login screen]] .\n\nThus, when you have  selected a module and the languages you want to be displayed, you can modify the module in various ways:\n\n- '''edit entries:''' Just click on the entry you want to modify in the overview, change the strings and confirm the change with \"OK\".\n\n- '''new entry:''' Click on \"new entry\" in the overview, enter the ID of the new entry, with a comment if appropriate. A new entry will always be created in ''all'' the  module languages at the same time. Usually, new entries will only be created by the system provider. \n\n- '''delete entry:''' Go into mask \"edit entry\" (see above) and click on \"delete entry\". When you have confirmed the command, the entry will be deleted in ''all'' languages. Usually, entries will only be deleted by the system provider.\n\n- '''new language:''' Click on \"new language\" in the overview and enter the ID of the new language - \"de\", \"en\", \"fr\", \"es\" etc. If you click on \"OK\", the language will be applied to ''all'' the entries defined in the module. When the new language has been created, these entries will  either be shown as empty or can then be initialised with the entries in an existing language.   \n\n- '''delete language:''' Go into mask \"edit entry\" (see above) and click on \"delete language\". When you confirm the command, the language you have selected will be deleted, together with ''all'' entries.\n\nSometimes you  may be informed that entries and/or languages cannot be modified. If that happens, you will have to alter or grant the '''access rights''' for the relevant files so that they can be written by PHP.");
